WEBVTT

00:02.741 --> 00:05.005
[Kristen gasping
and panting loudly]

00:05.048 --> 00:07.311
DAVID: Repeat after me.
I am firmly resolved,

00:07.355 --> 00:10.793
-with the help of Thy grace...
-[crying]

00:10.836 --> 00:14.666
to sin no more and to avoid
the near occasion of sin.

00:14.710 --> 00:16.320
I firmly resolve to sin no more

00:16.364 --> 00:18.757
and to avoid the near occasion
of sin. [crying]

00:18.801 --> 00:20.324
-Amen.
-Amen.

00:20.368 --> 00:22.326
I absolve you from your sins

00:22.370 --> 00:24.850
in the name of the Father,

00:24.894 --> 00:28.202
and of the Son
and of the Holy Spirit.

00:28.245 --> 00:29.768
[crying]

00:29.812 --> 00:31.857
Amen.

00:35.470 --> 00:37.428
[sobbing]

00:37.472 --> 00:38.908
It's okay.

00:38.951 --> 00:41.084
Shh...

00:41.128 --> 00:43.521
-[Kristen breathes loudly]
-[David inhales]

00:43.565 --> 00:46.263
It's okay.

00:46.307 --> 00:48.526
-[sighs]
-DAVID: It's over.

00:50.659 --> 00:52.617
DAVID:
Hmm.

00:52.661 --> 00:55.272
[David breathing deeply]

01:32.396 --> 01:34.616
[Kristen breathes shakily]

01:39.403 --> 01:41.840
[Kristen sighs]

01:42.798 --> 01:45.235
[both panting]

01:58.205 --> 02:00.120
[panting]

02:06.213 --> 02:08.258
I'm sorry.

02:09.303 --> 02:11.218
No, no, no, it's...

02:11.261 --> 02:13.263
-It's my fault.
-I'm so sorry.

02:13.307 --> 02:15.004
-I'm so sorry.
-It's my fault. No.

02:15.047 --> 02:16.875
Wait.

02:16.919 --> 02:18.529
Kristen!

02:31.325 --> 02:33.414
[panting]

02:36.025 --> 02:38.723
-[yelling]
-[glass breaking, clattering]

02:42.118 --> 02:44.164
[whispering]:
Oh, help me, God.

02:45.774 --> 02:47.819
Help me, God.

02:47.863 --> 02:49.952
[inhales sharply]

02:54.304 --> 02:56.350
[panting]

02:58.743 --> 03:01.181
Help me.

03:03.879 --> 03:05.924
Oh, God.

03:08.492 --> 03:10.625
[quietly]:
Help me.

03:14.281 --> 03:16.674
Help me.

03:17.762 --> 03:19.895
Don't look.

03:19.938 --> 03:22.419
Don't turn.

03:22.463 --> 03:24.552
We're doing this.

03:24.595 --> 03:26.597
We won't talk about it.

03:26.641 --> 03:29.296
We won't mention it, ever.

03:29.339 --> 03:32.081
We won't act on it again.

03:32.124 --> 03:33.778
We can't.

03:33.822 --> 03:35.780
I want you, David.

03:35.824 --> 03:38.957
I want you more
than anyone I've ever wanted.

03:39.001 --> 03:41.830
And I'm not leaving here
until you fuck me.

03:42.787 --> 03:44.485
[Kristen sighs]

03:44.528 --> 03:46.617
[David panting]

03:48.271 --> 03:50.230
Just this once.

03:50.273 --> 03:52.362
[David moans]

03:52.406 --> 03:54.495
Shh.

04:04.200 --> 04:06.202
[train whistle blows]

04:09.510 --> 04:10.641
-Mom!
-Ready, Mom!

04:10.685 --> 04:12.252
-Mom!
-Where's Mom?

04:12.295 --> 04:13.731
-Mom!
-Let us in.

04:13.775 --> 04:15.472
-Mom!
-Will you sign my paper...?

04:15.516 --> 04:16.995
-LAURA: I got her...
-[indistinct chatter]

04:19.389 --> 04:21.609
What's wrong? What did Lexis do?

04:21.652 --> 04:23.219
Nothing. We were just talking.

04:23.263 --> 04:24.655
-Well, she's the favorite child.
-[overlapping chatter]

04:24.699 --> 04:26.135
Okay, shh. I need you

04:26.178 --> 04:27.876
to listen to me for a second.

04:27.919 --> 04:29.312
-But we'll be late.
-Well, then,

04:29.356 --> 04:30.705
Grandma can drive you.
This is important.

04:30.748 --> 04:33.316
-Okay.
-Lexis and I have made a pact.

04:33.360 --> 04:35.362
And we need your help
to make it come true.

04:35.405 --> 04:39.496
Leland Townsend has been
approaching Lexis after school.

04:40.454 --> 04:43.674
None of you look surprised, so
my guess is you knew about this?

04:43.718 --> 04:45.197
[overlapping chatter]

04:45.241 --> 04:46.677
Okay, okay, it's a new day.
It's okay.

04:46.721 --> 04:48.810
I want you all to understand:

04:48.853 --> 04:50.812
this man intends to hurt us.

04:50.855 --> 04:54.337
He's a bad man,
and he's declared a war on us.

04:54.381 --> 04:57.514
And I need the four of you
to work together to stop him.

04:57.558 --> 04:59.734
Now Leland gave Lexis this note.

04:59.777 --> 05:01.649
Do any of you know
what this means?

05:01.692 --> 05:03.694
-LAURA: Daffodil? No.
-LILA: Isn't it a flower, Mom?

05:03.738 --> 05:05.348
-I think it's a...
-I have no idea...

05:05.392 --> 05:08.351
Shh. I'm talking to you
like more mature girls now

05:08.395 --> 05:10.005
because I need you all to be.

05:10.048 --> 05:13.791
Okay? If Leland approaches
Lexis again,

05:13.835 --> 05:16.272
or any of you, you tell me.

05:16.316 --> 05:17.969
Not in a week, not in a day.

05:18.013 --> 05:20.407
You call me that very instant.

05:20.450 --> 05:22.757
Do you understand?

05:22.800 --> 05:24.541
-Yeah.
-KRISTEN: Okay.

05:24.585 --> 05:25.977
Good. Then give me a hug.

05:26.021 --> 05:27.501
Hey, but we have to be quick.

05:27.544 --> 05:29.241
-[chattering]
-I love you. Now get to school.

05:29.285 --> 05:30.721
-All right. Go, go, go, go.
-[overlapping chatter]

05:30.765 --> 05:32.375
Let's get to school.
I love you all so much.

05:32.419 --> 05:33.724
-So much.
-LILA: Grandma?

05:33.768 --> 05:34.943
-LEXIS: Thank you. Bye, Mom.
-Bye.

05:34.986 --> 05:37.075
[footsteps running]

05:37.119 --> 05:39.469
-Mom?
-Yeah?

05:39.513 --> 05:42.646
I might have something for you.

05:42.690 --> 05:45.562
[loud beep,
rhythmic rattling]

05:50.350 --> 05:52.961
Wow. I didn't know
you were this far along.

05:53.004 --> 05:54.963
Yes. We're ready. Tonight.

05:55.006 --> 05:57.618
We keep it
at 43 degrees in here.

05:57.661 --> 05:59.663
Are they looking for money
from the Church?

05:59.707 --> 06:01.186
No. They want a body.

06:01.230 --> 06:03.101
-[beep, door rattling]
-Where's Kristen?

06:03.145 --> 06:05.408
-Thought she'd be here.
-Probably running late.

06:05.452 --> 06:07.410
Getting the girls off to school.

06:07.454 --> 06:09.412
BEVERLY: Up ahead,
you'll notice the capsule

06:09.456 --> 06:11.327
where the subject's body
will go.

06:11.371 --> 06:14.199
The lab environment is so large
to prevent outside heat

06:14.243 --> 06:16.071
or radiation from interfering
with our results.

06:16.114 --> 06:17.638
BEN:
It all seems a bit inexact.

06:17.681 --> 06:19.596
It's all thermo-insulated
to eliminate the exchange

06:19.640 --> 06:21.163
of radiant energy
and radiation.

06:21.206 --> 06:23.165
And underneath the capsule--
what's this?

06:23.208 --> 06:25.602
A mass spectrometer,

06:25.646 --> 06:28.344
sensitive down
to one septillionth of a gram.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.868
So you're weighing the body
at the moment of death?

06:30.912 --> 06:32.566
And that'll tell you what?

06:32.609 --> 06:34.872
You believe a human body
just ends at death, correct?

06:34.916 --> 06:36.396
-BEN: Yup.
-Then, in theory,

06:36.439 --> 06:37.658
there should be no loss
of mass or energy

06:37.701 --> 06:38.746
when a person dies.

06:38.789 --> 06:39.964
The first law of thermodynamics:

06:40.008 --> 06:41.313
the body should weigh the same

06:41.357 --> 06:42.619
immediately after death
as before.

06:42.663 --> 06:43.664
Well, except for an exhalation

06:43.707 --> 06:45.013
of breath and other fluids.

06:45.056 --> 06:46.536
Feces, urine.

06:46.580 --> 06:48.277
But they'll all
be trapped in this container,

06:48.320 --> 06:49.931
and weighed before
and after death.

06:49.974 --> 06:52.150
My experiment is about the loss
of mass or energy

06:52.194 --> 06:53.543
that
there is no explanation for.

06:53.587 --> 06:56.024
You want to measure
for the soul?

06:56.067 --> 06:58.200
BEVERLY:
I am not a religious person.

06:58.243 --> 06:59.723
You call it a soul,

06:59.767 --> 07:02.726
but I am measuring for...
consciousness.

07:02.770 --> 07:05.207
If there is a loss of
body weight when a person dies,

07:05.250 --> 07:06.556
what is it?

07:06.600 --> 07:08.732
What does it weigh?
Where does it go?

07:08.776 --> 07:10.908
Hmm. And if it weighs the same?

07:11.953 --> 07:14.521
Then there's nothing else
to discuss.

07:14.564 --> 07:16.653
There is nothing after death.

07:20.483 --> 07:22.877
BEN:
In 1901, a physician

07:22.920 --> 07:25.445
named Duncan MacDougall
conducted an experiment

07:25.488 --> 07:28.056
into the weight of the...

07:28.099 --> 07:29.623
soul.

07:29.666 --> 07:33.757
He conducted an experiment
with dying subjects

07:33.801 --> 07:35.498
and weighed them
before and after death.

07:35.542 --> 07:38.501
He found a difference
of 21 grams.

07:38.545 --> 07:41.722
And has this experiment
been retried since?

07:41.765 --> 07:43.463
-BEN: No.
-KORECKI: Why not?

07:43.506 --> 07:45.856
BEN: It was seen
as scientifically unserious.

07:45.900 --> 07:47.597
KORECKI:
Because it was about the soul?

07:47.641 --> 07:49.730
No. Because science doesn't
have a religious agenda.

07:49.773 --> 07:51.514
DAVID: If it doesn't have
a religious agenda, then

07:51.558 --> 07:53.603
why doesn't it try
to replicate the experiment?

07:53.647 --> 07:56.258
Because you're trying
to use science as a crutch.

07:56.301 --> 07:58.434
You're trying to use it to prove
there's life after death.

07:58.478 --> 08:00.175
DAVID: No, but why isn't it
treated the same way

08:00.218 --> 08:01.524
-as quantum physics?
-Quantum physics?

08:01.568 --> 08:03.047
It doesn't have
a religious agenda.

08:03.091 --> 08:04.701
It's not trying
to prove there's religion.

08:04.745 --> 08:05.876
-All right, all right, stop.
-Yes, but that's why...

08:05.920 --> 08:07.835
Stop. This Dr. Swan--

08:07.878 --> 08:09.401
she doesn't want money from us?

08:09.445 --> 08:11.012
No. She-she wants people
who are dying.

08:11.055 --> 08:12.535
[door opens]

08:13.623 --> 08:15.799
[footsteps approaching]

08:16.844 --> 08:18.802
Don't stop on my account.

08:18.846 --> 08:20.891
Go ahead, David.

08:20.935 --> 08:23.459
I have, uh... I don't have
anything else to say.

08:23.503 --> 08:26.418
Well, there is a priest
in hospice care.

08:26.462 --> 08:28.986
He has ASPS, a very rare cancer.

08:29.030 --> 08:31.554
The doctors say
he has 24 hours to live.

08:31.598 --> 08:36.516
I talked to him about this
experiment, and he volunteered.

08:37.517 --> 08:38.909
Thoughts?

08:38.953 --> 08:40.607
[Leland clears throat]

08:40.650 --> 08:44.306
Let me try to clear
the air here, if you don't mind,

08:44.349 --> 08:46.047
-Your Eminence.
-Please.

08:46.090 --> 08:49.224
David, I know that you and I got
off on the wrong foot,

08:49.267 --> 08:50.617
but I've been asked
by the cardinal

08:50.660 --> 08:52.444
to look over your shoulder

08:52.488 --> 08:54.534
for issues of liability.

08:54.577 --> 08:58.363
Liability is a cross
we all have to bear.

09:02.846 --> 09:04.892
Hi.

09:04.935 --> 09:07.808
-I'm sorry I'm late.
-KORECKI: That's perfectly fine.

09:07.851 --> 09:10.680
We've been discussing
this soul scale experiment.

09:10.724 --> 09:12.377
LELAND: And the need
for a signed release

09:12.421 --> 09:13.901
from the participating priest.

09:13.944 --> 09:16.599
Yes, Ms. Bouchard?

09:16.643 --> 09:18.601
-Hello.
-Hello.

09:18.645 --> 09:21.169
Would you mind backing up
a few feet?

09:21.212 --> 09:23.519
[Leland laughs]

09:27.654 --> 09:29.612
-What is this?
-A restraining order.

09:29.656 --> 09:31.614
You've been served.

09:31.658 --> 09:36.010
Monsignor, can't we settle
our disagreements

09:36.053 --> 09:37.881
without these
ad hominem attacks?

09:37.925 --> 09:39.230
Ms. Bouchard,
this is not necessary.

09:39.274 --> 09:40.797
Oh, it's not a restraining order
for me.

09:40.841 --> 09:43.234
I can take care of myself.

09:43.278 --> 09:44.714
It's for
my 11-year-old daughter.

09:44.758 --> 09:47.587
-Excuse me?
-KRISTEN: Mr. Townsend

09:47.630 --> 09:48.979
has approached my daughter
at school

09:49.023 --> 09:50.590
on four separate occasions,

09:50.633 --> 09:52.069
and he's asked her
to keep it a secret from me.

09:52.113 --> 09:53.723
No, this is...

09:53.767 --> 09:55.551
And he's also made her
uncomfortable with his touch.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.640
I did not. What are you
talking about? This is insane.

09:57.684 --> 10:00.164
Luckily, one of my daughters
took a photo,

10:00.208 --> 10:03.472
and that is why the court
granted me this injunction.

10:03.515 --> 10:07.345
That... that is
a misinterpretation.

10:07.389 --> 10:08.825
Well, I guess it's a good thing

10:08.869 --> 10:10.305
that the Catholic Church
has no issues

10:10.348 --> 10:11.698
with older men
touching children.

10:11.741 --> 10:13.351
[clears throat]

10:13.395 --> 10:15.876
Leland, let's step outside
for a second.

10:15.919 --> 10:18.443
No, this is...
this is a lie, Your Eminence.

10:18.487 --> 10:20.271
-This is just...
-Like you said, Leland,

10:20.315 --> 10:22.665
liability is a cross
we all have to bear.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.928
[plays opening notes
of "Beethoven's 5th Symphony"]

10:24.972 --> 10:27.104
Let's just talk for a second.

10:30.194 --> 10:31.631
-You okay?
-Yeah.

10:31.674 --> 10:33.154
Is everything all right
with Lexis?

10:33.197 --> 10:35.547
We're getting back on track.

10:37.071 --> 10:39.639
And everything else?

10:40.683 --> 10:42.250
Yeah, we're good.

10:43.251 --> 10:45.035
Good.

10:48.822 --> 10:51.302
Ms. Bouchard, I've asked Leland

10:51.346 --> 10:53.348
to take a step back
until we can investigate.

10:53.391 --> 10:55.045
KRISTEN:
Thank you, Your Eminence.

10:55.089 --> 10:57.395
No, thank you for your patience.

10:57.439 --> 10:59.528
And, David,
if you have a moment,

10:59.571 --> 11:01.138
I need you to hear a confession.

11:02.096 --> 11:04.359
How are you?

11:04.402 --> 11:06.970
Embarrassed at everybody
making a fuss.

11:07.014 --> 11:09.364
Who's that?

11:09.407 --> 11:14.151
Our newest priest,
David Acosta.

11:14.195 --> 11:15.631
I wanted him
to hear your confession.

11:15.675 --> 11:17.024
Well, you can.

11:17.067 --> 11:19.417
No, no,
we're too good of friends.

11:19.461 --> 11:21.724
So what's the word?

11:21.768 --> 11:24.727
-Have I been approved?
-You have.

11:24.771 --> 11:27.295
But it's going
to be a very isolated death,

11:27.338 --> 11:29.514
I wanted to warn you.

11:29.558 --> 11:31.168
You have to lie alone
in a chamber.

11:31.212 --> 11:33.301
I'll be fine.

11:33.344 --> 11:38.045
How much do you think
my soul will weigh?

11:38.088 --> 11:39.786
[laughs]

11:39.829 --> 11:41.918
[whispering]:
You'll be a heavyweight.

11:41.962 --> 11:44.181
[chuckles]

11:44.225 --> 11:46.314
David?

11:52.581 --> 11:56.019
Father, forgive me,
for I have sinned.

11:56.063 --> 11:59.675
I've had...
I've had impure thoughts.

11:59.719 --> 12:02.504
Celibacy has been difficult
for me.

12:04.811 --> 12:07.770
It's difficult for everyone.

12:07.814 --> 12:11.905
IGNATIUS:
No, my mind is full of lust.

12:13.254 --> 12:17.780
Thoughts of being held, holding,

12:17.824 --> 12:21.175
that my life was pointless
without love.

12:23.786 --> 12:26.006
You have God's love.

12:26.963 --> 12:30.140
I never felt it.

12:30.184 --> 12:32.403
I prayed for it.

12:32.447 --> 12:35.232
But what if
there's just darkness, and

12:35.276 --> 12:39.759
I spent my life being an idiot?

12:42.283 --> 12:44.372
I don't want to die.

12:44.415 --> 12:47.114
[exhales]

12:50.682 --> 12:54.425
God will defend
and protect you.

13:12.966 --> 13:14.706
[train cars chugging]

13:43.474 --> 13:45.563
[upbeat, whimsical
instrumental music plays]

14:04.887 --> 14:07.324
GAME VOICE: Congratulations,
Lynda the Lizard.

14:07.368 --> 14:09.370
There are other animals
who want to be your friend.

14:09.413 --> 14:11.502
Do you want to meet them?

14:14.636 --> 14:18.422
[two dings]

14:19.946 --> 14:22.122
Hello, Lynda.
I'm Pollie the Pig.

14:22.165 --> 14:25.865
And I welcome you.
Have you built your house yet?

14:30.086 --> 14:32.262
No.

14:33.524 --> 14:35.613
Let me show you
where you should build.

14:37.267 --> 14:38.878
How old are you, Lynda?

14:45.797 --> 14:48.931
-11. What about you?
-I'm 12.

14:48.975 --> 14:51.586
My parents are divorced.
Are yours?

14:53.544 --> 14:56.069
LYNDA:
No, but my dad is away a lot.

14:57.287 --> 14:58.985
That sucks.

14:59.028 --> 15:01.988
I like having someone
to talk to. How about you?

15:02.031 --> 15:03.641
-Me, too.
-SHERYL: Hello?

15:03.685 --> 15:05.252
Your mom just called.

15:05.295 --> 15:07.950
-Hey, where are the girls?
-I'm a girl.

15:07.994 --> 15:10.083
Yes, but where are
the other girls? Your sisters.

15:10.126 --> 15:12.085
Backyard?

15:12.128 --> 15:14.087
Okay. Well, come on.
I'm ordering pizza.

15:14.130 --> 15:15.523
-Your mom has to work late.
-Doing what?

15:15.566 --> 15:17.655
I don't know.
Demon stuff. Let's go.

15:17.699 --> 15:19.657
♪

15:21.703 --> 15:25.141
I have to go.
I'll see you tomorrow.

15:25.185 --> 15:27.927
I can't wait. I'm lonely.

15:29.363 --> 15:31.452
LYNDA:
Me, too.

15:33.497 --> 15:36.979
LYON: What do you have?
Give me a signal.

15:38.676 --> 15:39.634
Let's go. Here he comes.
Let's get ready.

15:39.677 --> 15:40.635
I'm sorry. Excuse me.

15:40.678 --> 15:42.071
Vitals are online.

15:42.115 --> 15:43.377
-I need a reading.
-BEVERLY: To the right.

15:43.420 --> 15:44.987
-To the right.
-MAN: Let's go!

15:45.031 --> 15:46.728
LYON: He is alert,
oriented to self only.

15:46.771 --> 15:49.339
This is feeling
very Frankenstein.

15:49.383 --> 15:52.038
Yeah? Well,
welcome to fringe science.

15:52.081 --> 15:54.518
Okay, the respirations
are still irregular.

15:54.562 --> 15:56.303
Pulse 110.
His lungs are shutting down.

15:56.346 --> 15:58.305
-The breathing is labored...
-We have to go, Father.

15:58.348 --> 16:00.524
Through this holy anointing,
may the Lord through his love

16:00.568 --> 16:02.439
and mercy help you with
the grace of the Holy Spirit.

16:02.483 --> 16:04.137
Tachycardia to the 130s,
hypertensive to the 80s...

16:04.180 --> 16:06.487
What? Where-where...?
What is this?

16:06.530 --> 16:08.576
-We're here, Frank.
-Monsignor, we don't have time.

16:08.619 --> 16:09.881
-Then make time.
-We don't have time.

16:09.925 --> 16:10.970
-LYON: He's losing
consciousness.

16:11.013 --> 16:12.232
-Father?
-LYON: Pulse 110.

16:12.275 --> 16:13.320
-His organs are shutting down.
-Ah.

16:13.363 --> 16:14.321
Do you still want to do this?

16:14.364 --> 16:16.236
-The experiment.
-Ah.

16:16.279 --> 16:17.846
Do you want to go forward?

16:17.889 --> 16:19.500
I don't want to die.

16:19.543 --> 16:21.806
I know.

