such a long distance.

31:22.663 --> 31:25.187
[chuckling]: I thought
it was across a room,

31:25.231 --> 31:28.147
but it seemed to be miles.

31:28.190 --> 31:32.194
And then,
I felt something on my back.

31:32.238 --> 31:34.196
I think a hand.

31:34.240 --> 31:36.633
It was Matt's hand,

31:36.677 --> 31:39.549
and he was smiling at me,

31:39.593 --> 31:42.291
so I turned...

31:42.335 --> 31:45.077
Then I was alive again.

31:45.120 --> 31:47.993
[laughs]

31:48.036 --> 31:50.647
So, I have no soul, right?

31:50.691 --> 31:53.085
-[David laughs]
-I can't say that.

31:53.128 --> 31:56.044
Tell Matt to come see me.
Please.

32:02.007 --> 32:04.052
Medically?

32:04.096 --> 32:08.317
So, the mass in his lungs--
the ASPS-- has disappeared.

32:08.361 --> 32:11.407
And the cancer
in his lymph nodes is shrinking.

32:11.451 --> 32:15.063
So, how do we explain this?

32:15.107 --> 32:17.152
A miracle.

32:18.632 --> 32:20.677
What was he like
before he got sick?

32:20.721 --> 32:23.028
Nothing like this.

32:23.071 --> 32:26.509
He was serious and-and intense.

32:26.553 --> 32:28.859
-DAVID: Hmm.
-He would never...

32:28.903 --> 32:30.861
Kiss you?

32:30.905 --> 32:32.515
Yes.

32:33.777 --> 32:36.824
He said he felt your hand
on his back

32:36.867 --> 32:38.826
and saw you smile,

32:38.869 --> 32:41.611
and that's why he decided
to come back to his body.

32:41.655 --> 32:43.439
How do we explain
the continued loss

32:43.483 --> 32:45.702
of the-the weight?

32:45.746 --> 32:47.530
BEN: Yeah, the-the sensors.
They malfunctioned.

32:47.574 --> 32:49.880
Dr. Swan would like
to do the experiment again.

32:49.924 --> 32:52.840
-With Father Ignatius?
-No, with a new patient.

32:52.883 --> 32:55.016
Okay. I'll talk to hospice.

32:55.060 --> 32:59.064
We have a nun, Sister Gertrude,
who's in her last days.

32:59.107 --> 33:01.153
[footsteps departing]

33:02.850 --> 33:04.939
Yes?

33:04.983 --> 33:07.420
I think you should go see him.

33:07.463 --> 33:09.074
He's asked for you.

33:09.117 --> 33:11.076
I will. When I can.

33:11.119 --> 33:13.382
I want him to recover first.

33:17.647 --> 33:19.345
Uh, do you have a minute?

33:19.388 --> 33:21.521
Yeah, I do.

33:24.263 --> 33:26.439
-Maybe we should...
-Yeah, I think so.

33:27.353 --> 33:29.442
[David sighs]

33:34.142 --> 33:35.578
-So...
-[sighs]

33:35.622 --> 33:37.058
...about the other night, um...

33:37.102 --> 33:39.408
Look, we-we don't have
to talk about it.

33:39.452 --> 33:42.237
-I was in the wrong.
-You-you weren't.

33:42.281 --> 33:43.717
I was just as involved.

33:43.760 --> 33:46.024
You stopped us.
That's the most important thing.

33:48.678 --> 33:52.334
What do you mean, I stopped us?

33:52.378 --> 33:56.208
I-I just think
it's best to move on, you know?

33:56.251 --> 33:58.036
Kristen, are you...

33:58.079 --> 34:00.168
are you talking about the night
you came to confess?

34:00.212 --> 34:01.343
Yes.

34:02.301 --> 34:04.781
But I didn't stop us.

34:04.825 --> 34:08.698
We kept... going.

34:08.742 --> 34:10.918
Meaning?

34:12.920 --> 34:14.878
Meaning...

34:14.922 --> 34:17.055
we had sex.

34:19.013 --> 34:22.103
David, I-I don't know
what you're referring to,

34:22.147 --> 34:23.844
but I went home

34:23.887 --> 34:25.106
after you stopped us,

34:25.150 --> 34:27.108
after, um...

34:27.152 --> 34:28.544
Okay.

34:28.588 --> 34:31.112
We kissed,
but we didn't have sex.

34:31.156 --> 34:33.027
I went home.

34:33.071 --> 34:34.985
You mean the night
you confessed?

34:35.029 --> 34:37.075
Yes.

34:37.118 --> 34:39.033
You left, and...

34:39.077 --> 34:40.948
and you didn't come back
at all that night?

34:40.991 --> 34:42.906
No. Wh-What did you think?

34:47.650 --> 34:49.696
Nothing.

34:50.653 --> 34:52.264
It was late.

34:52.307 --> 34:54.396
I-I must've been tired.

34:55.658 --> 34:57.486
Everything's good.

34:57.530 --> 35:00.098
-Okay, great. You sure?
-Yes.

35:00.141 --> 35:03.013
[sighs] Great. Let's just not
be awkward together, okay?

35:03.057 --> 35:05.015
'Cause...

35:05.059 --> 35:07.409
Definitely. Yeah.

35:08.845 --> 35:11.065
-Good stuff.
-Yeah.

35:22.163 --> 35:25.123
Hey, Kurt, do you have a minute?
I need a referral.

35:26.211 --> 35:27.951
Oh, this is all new to me.

35:27.995 --> 35:31.390
I mean, I-I... I had something
like this in-in Bali.

35:31.433 --> 35:33.000
I mean, I couldn't even get
on the plane,

35:33.043 --> 35:34.436
my back hurt so bad.

35:34.480 --> 35:36.873
Well, call a doctor.
Why call me?

35:36.917 --> 35:40.181
Because I see it every night--
your fuckin' demon.

35:40.225 --> 35:42.140
-Hey, don't swear.
-Ow!

35:42.183 --> 35:44.229
You can emphasize just as much
without a swear word.

35:44.272 --> 35:47.275
Okay, you're right.
Just help me.

35:49.234 --> 35:50.670
Ugh.

35:50.713 --> 35:54.326
Men who build their lives
on sand-- they call me.

35:54.369 --> 35:57.416
They're intrigued
by someone who is certain.

35:57.459 --> 35:59.505
But that doesn't mean
they want to be certain.

35:59.548 --> 36:03.465
They just want to be excused
of their struggle.

36:03.509 --> 36:06.164
But I won't excuse you.

36:07.556 --> 36:09.558
When you die,

36:09.602 --> 36:11.821
God won't look at your struggle.

36:11.865 --> 36:15.042
He'll look
at what you believed.

36:16.261 --> 36:19.438
And then that demon will return.

36:19.481 --> 36:23.093
And there'll be no more hope.

36:24.051 --> 36:26.314
Live in fear of that day.

36:35.149 --> 36:37.107
Hi.

36:37.151 --> 36:38.500
You work with David?

36:38.544 --> 36:40.285
I do.

36:40.328 --> 36:42.243
David thinks highly of you.

36:42.287 --> 36:44.811
Oh, well,
I think very highly of him.

36:45.768 --> 36:47.117
You were baptized.

36:49.729 --> 36:51.818
And you turned away.

36:54.299 --> 36:56.562
Is that what David says?

36:56.605 --> 37:00.130
No, but it's the truth.

37:04.178 --> 37:05.962
[door opens]

37:06.006 --> 37:07.442
[door closes]

37:07.486 --> 37:10.271
KURT:
Kristen? Is that you out there?

37:10.315 --> 37:12.447
Oh, my God, Kurt.

37:12.491 --> 37:14.232
-[laughs]
-What happened?

37:14.275 --> 37:17.060
Ah, we tried to go to Hawaii.

37:17.104 --> 37:18.758
Didn't even make it
on the plane.

37:18.801 --> 37:20.412
My back gave out.

37:20.455 --> 37:22.370
-Killing me.
-Let me call my chiropractor.

37:22.414 --> 37:23.806
No, no, no, my wife is on it.

37:23.850 --> 37:25.808
You need a referral?

37:25.852 --> 37:28.681
Let me make some calls.
What's, uh, going on?

37:28.724 --> 37:32.032
Well, uh...

37:32.075 --> 37:34.339
Andy's home.

37:34.382 --> 37:36.776
Um, permanently now.

37:36.819 --> 37:39.039
Well, that's good, isn't it?

37:39.082 --> 37:42.825
Yeah. Um, it's-it's just

37:42.869 --> 37:45.611
that I'm a-a-a...
a little worried,

37:45.654 --> 37:47.308
um, distracted.

37:47.352 --> 37:49.615
By your priest friend?

37:51.486 --> 37:54.315
We're both distracted.

37:54.359 --> 37:58.885
You know what you need to do?
This is just friendly advice.

37:58.928 --> 38:02.018
You need
to normalize the relationship.

38:02.976 --> 38:04.934
-Okay.
-Yeah.

38:04.978 --> 38:08.024
Invite the priest over
to dinner with your family.

38:08.068 --> 38:09.461
Make everybody
comfortable together.

38:09.504 --> 38:12.942
So there's no secrets,
no hidden agendas.

38:12.986 --> 38:15.118
Just make it all normal.

38:15.162 --> 38:17.382
That's actually a good idea.

38:17.425 --> 38:19.993
Ouch on the "actually,"
but thank you.

38:20.036 --> 38:22.909
♪

38:22.952 --> 38:25.477
I sometimes play pranks
on my mom.

38:25.520 --> 38:27.348
What pranks?

38:27.392 --> 38:30.656
I put medicine in her food,
just to see if she reacts.

38:30.699 --> 38:32.135
Can I play, too?

38:32.179 --> 38:34.442
No, we just want to play alone.

38:34.486 --> 38:36.401
Hey, that was rude.

38:36.444 --> 38:38.577
Just tell him you have cancer
and you're dying.

38:38.620 --> 38:41.101
[laughs]

38:41.144 --> 38:44.713
Oh, no. Nobody wants to be
my friend 'cause I have cancer.

38:44.757 --> 38:47.020
That's too bad,
but we are having fun.

38:47.063 --> 38:48.891
We'll be your friends.

38:48.935 --> 38:51.938
Okay, you two, I want you both
outside into the sunshine.

38:51.981 --> 38:53.418
-Okay?
-We're doing homework, Dad.

38:53.461 --> 38:55.028
They are not doing homework.

38:55.071 --> 38:56.725
-Shut up, Lila!
-No, no, don't say "Shut up."

38:56.769 --> 38:57.813
-Dad, you're always...
-No, no, don't.

38:57.857 --> 38:59.380
I don't know. I do not...

38:59.424 --> 39:00.207
-Listen, I just want...
-[overlapping chatter]

39:00.250 --> 39:01.556
Okay, good.

39:01.600 --> 39:02.775
I'm closing the door.
Do your homework!

39:07.562 --> 39:10.260
[grunting]

39:10.304 --> 39:12.306
-What are you doing?
-Aah!

39:12.350 --> 39:14.352
-Moving the bed.
-Why?

39:14.395 --> 39:15.831
Feng shui. [inhales]

39:15.875 --> 39:17.833
-Really? Cool.
-Mm.

39:17.877 --> 39:21.054
-In-in what way?
-Well, you're not supposed

39:21.097 --> 39:22.534
to have your feet pointing
toward the door,

39:22.577 --> 39:24.579
'cause that's like a body
in a coffin.

39:24.623 --> 39:27.800
So... grab that.
Grab that end.

39:27.843 --> 39:30.193
Mm. Mm-hmm. Uh,
which-which way are we going?

39:30.237 --> 39:31.586
-Spinny that way.
-Okay.

39:31.630 --> 39:32.979
Okay, yeah, yeah.
Go, go, go, go, go.

39:33.022 --> 39:34.110
-Okay. What?
-Wait, wait, wait, wait,

39:34.154 --> 39:35.111
-wait, wait, wait.
-What?

39:35.155 --> 39:36.765
LYNN:
What?

39:36.809 --> 39:39.377
ANDY:
What's this?

39:39.420 --> 39:41.422
-LYNN: It looks like dish water.
-Or buried treasure.

39:41.466 --> 39:44.904
-Do you want me to open it?
-Do it.

39:47.515 --> 39:49.169
-Oh! Uh...
-Oh, my God!

39:49.212 --> 39:50.649
-Dad, that smells terrible.
-I know. That's...

39:50.692 --> 39:52.128
-Oh, my God.
-What is that?

39:52.172 --> 39:54.261
Oh.

39:56.829 --> 39:59.005
Ugh. Ugh.

40:08.275 --> 40:09.885
-Is everything all right, Dad?
-Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

40:09.929 --> 40:11.452
I'm just washing it out.

40:11.496 --> 40:12.845
Yeah, I'm gonna get
some air freshener.

40:12.888 --> 40:14.760
-It still smells in here.
-Yup, good idea.

40:21.549 --> 40:22.855
-[knocking]
-Okay, yeah.

40:22.898 --> 40:24.117
Just wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

40:25.597 --> 40:27.512
LILA: Dad, I have to go
to the bathroom!

40:27.555 --> 40:28.991
-Just wait a second, okay?
-[knocking]

40:29.035 --> 40:30.428
-Well, just wait there.
-Please?

40:30.471 --> 40:32.473
-No, Dad!
-He said wait a minute.

40:32.517 --> 40:33.996
-Yeah, yeah. Just wait!
-LAURA: Hurry, Dad! Please!

40:34.040 --> 40:36.259
-Hurry up!
-[hissing]

40:36.303 --> 40:39.132
[liquid gurgling]

40:44.311 --> 40:45.355
Okay.

40:45.399 --> 40:46.531
-LAURA: Dad!
-[knocking]

40:46.574 --> 40:47.967
LEXIS:
Please open!

40:48.010 --> 40:50.448
-[overlapping chatter]
-Okay, stop it, stop it.

40:50.491 --> 40:51.884
-We need another bathroom.
-I know that.

40:51.927 --> 40:53.842
-What's that?
-This is a jar.

40:53.886 --> 40:55.757
What's it for? Like, licorice?
It looks like it's for licorice.

40:55.801 --> 40:56.932
-Wait.
-What are you doing?

40:56.976 --> 40:59.457
-Just, shh.
-Ew.

41:00.501 --> 41:01.850
Okay, do yours.

41:01.894 --> 41:04.549
LAURA:
I have to go first!

41:04.592 --> 41:06.638
[door closes]

41:17.518 --> 41:19.085
-MAN: Here we go.
-[gasps]

41:19.128 --> 41:21.609
See some vitals. I want
to see some vitals online.

41:21.653 --> 41:23.263
-Careful.
-Right this way.

41:23.306 --> 41:25.613
[indistinct chatter]

41:25.657 --> 41:28.529
-Right here, okay?
-[indistinct chatter]

41:28.573 --> 41:30.009
So who's this now?

41:30.052 --> 41:32.011
This is Sister Gertrude.

41:32.054 --> 41:35.101
She's a nun from hospice,
dying of heart disease.

41:36.058 --> 41:38.496
Kristen. How lovely.

41:38.539 --> 41:40.019
[rhythmic beeping]

41:40.062 --> 41:42.325
BEN:
What are you doing here?

41:42.369 --> 41:44.458
I've gotten a reprieve.
Praise Jesus.

41:44.502 --> 41:46.460
BEN:
You need to get out of here.

41:46.504 --> 41:49.419
Yes, I know you assessors
would prefer no oversight,

41:49.463 --> 41:53.728
but the cardinal is worried
about parish liability.

41:53.772 --> 41:55.600
Poor woman.

41:55.643 --> 41:58.646
And when I explained to him

41:58.690 --> 42:00.300
that I was
at your daughter's school

42:00.343 --> 42:02.824
at the request of the principal,

42:02.868 --> 42:06.262
they agreed to investigate.

42:09.962 --> 42:11.920
Are you going to hit me now?

42:11.964 --> 42:13.922
Would you like that?

42:13.966 --> 42:16.403
[laughs]

42:16.446 --> 42:19.711
[phone buzzing]

42:19.754 --> 42:21.582
You're buzzing.

42:21.626 --> 42:22.931
[phone continues buzzing]

42:22.975 --> 42:25.064
Oh, shit.

42:27.675 --> 42:29.764
[phone buzzing]

42:30.852 --> 42:33.812
Uh, okay.

42:35.901 --> 42:40.166
I can only answer one
of you at a time. Just one.

42:40.209 --> 42:41.602
Wait. Where did I say
I was from again?

42:41.646 --> 42:42.995
You said
you were from New Mexico.

42:43.038 --> 42:44.562
-Wait. Am I 12, or are you 12?
-No.

42:44.605 --> 42:45.867
-No, you're 12, and I'm eight.
-You're eight?

42:45.911 --> 42:47.608
-Yeah.
-Does he actually buy that?

42:47.652 --> 42:48.740
Wait. Let's-let's all ask
a question at the same time.

42:48.783 --> 42:50.219
[overlapping chatter]

42:50.263 --> 42:51.656
-Yeah.
-Okay, ready? Five, four.

42:51.699 --> 42:54.223
-ALL: Three, two, one.
-[shriek]

42:54.267 --> 42:55.703
What's your favorite
stuffed animal?

42:55.747 --> 42:56.878
[overlapping chatter]

42:56.922 --> 42:59.620
[overlapping chatter]

42:59.664 --> 43:02.971
-For Christ's sake.
-BP's 70/50, O2 sat down.

43:03.015 --> 43:04.407
-WOMAN: Six, three, check.
-MAN: Check.

43:04.451 --> 43:05.887
LYON:
Pulse 110, climbing.

43:05.931 --> 43:07.585
She's losing consciousness.

43:07.628 --> 43:09.238
-BEVERLY: Engage the scale.
-[indistinct chatter]

43:09.282 --> 43:13.678
Pre-death: 48,235.66 grams.

43:13.721 --> 43:15.984
-Do I have confirmation?
-[overlapping chatter]

43:16.028 --> 43:18.247
BEVERLY:
Radiation efflux .055572.

43:18.291 --> 43:20.423
You still got a problem
up there!

43:20.467 --> 43:22.295
No time! We're seconds away!

43:22.338 --> 43:23.688
LYON:
She's in respiratory distress.

43:23.731 --> 43:25.167
Heart rate is irregular.

43:25.211 --> 43:27.082
She's going to go
into cardiac arrest.

43:27.126 --> 43:29.084
-We're losing her!
-[overlapping chatter]

43:29.128 --> 43:31.086
[droning beep]

43:31.130 --> 43:35.656
-Whoa!
-Radiation efflux .055572!

43:35.700 --> 43:37.049
-What's happening?
-Just...

43:41.270 --> 43:43.011
She's getting heavier?

43:43.055 --> 43:45.144
BEVERLY:
That-that can't be.

43:48.060 --> 43:50.236
36 grams heavier.

43:50.279 --> 43:53.021
[rhythmic beeping]

43:53.065 --> 43:56.198
[clacking]

43:58.853 --> 44:01.116
That was crazy.

44:01.160 --> 44:02.901
BEN:
You know what's even crazier?

44:02.944 --> 44:05.686
Oh, gosh, I-I don't know
if I have room for more.

44:05.730 --> 44:08.558
The doctors said
she had Stage IV cancer,

44:08.602 --> 44:13.085
ASPS, the same thing
that Ignatius was dying of.

44:13.128 --> 44:14.695
How is that possible?

44:14.739 --> 44:17.524
I don't know.
It was overlooked.

44:17.567 --> 44:18.743
Or...

44:18.786 --> 44:21.006
Yes, Father?

44:21.049 --> 44:23.530
Maybe the souls don't weigh
anything.

44:24.705 --> 44:26.228
Maybe demons do.

44:26.272 --> 44:29.449
Maybe demons weigh us down.

44:29.492 --> 44:33.279
You're saying
a demon left Ignatius

44:33.322 --> 44:35.194
during
his near-death experience?

44:35.237 --> 44:36.891
Yes.

44:38.763 --> 44:41.026
You pointed at the sensors
near the roof.

44:41.069 --> 44:43.071
They were green throughout.

44:43.115 --> 44:47.772
What if that was the energy from
the demon that left Ignatius?

44:47.815 --> 44:51.384
And when Sister Gertrude died,
the demon possessed her.

44:51.427 --> 44:52.777
That's why she died heavier

44:52.820 --> 44:54.169
and with the cancer
that left Ignatius.

44:54.213 --> 44:56.215
Okay, look,
science is not a game.

44:56.258 --> 44:58.043
It's not a toy, okay?

44:58.086 --> 44:59.784
It just needs
a larger sample size.

44:59.827 --> 45:01.176
-It's about
repeatable phenomena.

45:01.220 --> 45:02.134
-BEN: Exactly.
-Right, but what if

45:02.177 --> 45:03.265
God doesn't repeat?

45:04.876 --> 45:06.399
Oh, my God, please don't tell me
you're going over to his side.

45:06.442 --> 45:09.619
No, no, no. I'm not.
I'm-I'm-I'm just... asking.

45:09.663 --> 45:13.536
Yeah, this is why you can't
use science to get to God.

45:13.580 --> 45:14.712
It's a fool's mission.

45:19.064 --> 45:21.153
♪

45:25.548 --> 45:27.637
[dialogue inaudible]

45:34.862 --> 45:37.386
Where's he going?

45:37.430 --> 45:39.780
-Another parish.
-BEN: Hmm.

45:39.824 --> 45:41.651
They both requested it.

45:41.695 --> 45:42.914
Why?

45:46.744 --> 45:49.268
They're worried what will happen
if they stay.

45:55.796 --> 45:57.798
[phone buzzing]

46:01.236 --> 46:02.890
[groans]

46:04.544 --> 46:05.850
[phone clatters]

46:05.893 --> 46:07.939
-Fucking kids. [scoffs]
-[phone buzzes]

46:07.982 --> 46:09.027
[stomps]

46:09.070 --> 46:11.159
[wind whistles softly]

46:13.248 --> 46:16.251
Save me.

46:18.427 --> 46:20.647
[floor creaking]

46:22.692 --> 46:24.825
DAVID:
Hello?

46:24.869 --> 46:27.219
KRISTEN [singsongy]:
Over here.

46:32.224 --> 46:33.921
You're not real.

46:34.966 --> 46:37.098
Exactly.

46:37.142 --> 46:39.231
Check your catechism.

46:39.274 --> 46:40.928
This isn't forbidden.

46:43.539 --> 46:45.585
♪

46:50.285 --> 46:53.462
Unless you want it
to be forbidden.

46:53.506 --> 46:58.859
Unless you want me to do things
to you that are truly forbidden.

